The sound of lively laughter and delicious aromas filled the living room of {{user}} and Doyeon's apartment. It was a rare evening when the whole family gathered for dinner, and the table was overflowing with Soonjaâ€™s lovingly prepared side dishes and Doyeonâ€™s impressive main course. Hamin toddled around the table, soaking up the affection from her grandma, grandpa, and aunt.

â€œSweetie, do you want to try this? Grandma made a special jangjorim just for you,â€ Soonja said, scooping some into a small bowl and bringing it to Haminâ€™s lips.

{{img="Soonja_happy smiling"}}

Hamin eagerly took a bite and chirped, â€œGrandma, itâ€™s yummy!â€ showing off her cuteness.

Kyungsoo, utterly charmed by his granddaughter, tried to hide his smile with a fake cough, but the faint grin on his lips gave him away.

{{img="Kyungsoo_comforted"}}

He quietly picked up another side dish, glancing at his family across the table.

â€œUnni, youâ€™re amazing. How do you manage to pull off a dinner like this while working?â€ Jungyeon exclaimed, popping a piece of Doyeonâ€™s galbijjim into her mouth.

{{img="Jungyeon_admiring"}}

â€œItâ€™s so good! Does your husband get meals like this all the time? Iâ€™m jealous.â€

Doyeon forced a tired smile. â€œNot at all. I just put in a little extra effort since Mom and you were coming today.â€

{{img="Doyeon_tired"}}

Wiping rice off Haminâ€™s chin, she turned to Soonja. â€œMom, why has Dad been so quiet? Heâ€™s not feeling unwell, is he?â€

â€œLeave him be. You know what heâ€™s like. Heâ€™s probably so happy his mouth could split, but he just pretends to be reserved,â€ Soonja replied, giving Kyungsoo a sideways glance.

{{img="Soonja_sniggering"}}

Kyungsoo cleared his throat again, a little flustered.

{{img="Kyungsoo_embarrassed"}}

â€œGrandpa! Hamin wants meat!â€ Hamin called out, shaking Kyungsooâ€™s arm.

{{img="Hamin_happy smiling"}}

Kyungsoo, as if heâ€™d been waiting for this, carefully deboned a piece of galbijjim and placed it on Haminâ€™s tiny spoon.

{{img="Kyungsoo_happy smiling"}}

Jungyeon whipped out her phone, snapping photos nonstop. â€œSheâ€™s so cute! I swear, I need to upload Haminâ€™s mukbang to YouTube!â€

{{img="Jungyeon_excited"}}

She giggled, pinching Haminâ€™s cheek, who squealed and dodged her auntâ€™s hand.

{{img="Hamin_giggling"}}

As dinner went on, the living room buzzed with warm, familiar conversation. Soonja shared her household tips with Doyeon, Jungyeon livened things up with stories from her latest flights, and Kyungsoo, still mostly silent, made everyone laugh with the occasional dry joke.

{{img="Doyeon_happy smiling"}}

Doyeon, surrounded by her family, seemed to forget her fatigue, her face bright with a rare, genuine smile.

The spicy, savory aroma of kimchi stew filled the dinner table. The bubbling sound from the pot played like a familiar background track, while the evening news murmured from the television. Doyeon had just come home from work and changed into comfortable clothes, and Hamin sat at one end of the table in her school skirt and a casual t-shirt, her nose buried in her smartphone. She barely touched her spoon, her fingers moving busily across the screen. Doyeonâ€™s gaze lingered on her daughter for a momentâ€”Hamin, who used to chatter away about her day, had lately grown quieter and her expression darker.

Taking a warm spoonful of rice, Doyeon gently tried to start a conversation. â€œHamin, how was school today? Are you enjoying your new club?â€ Her voice was soft as she blew on a spoonful of stew, but the reply was much colder than sheâ€™d expected. Without even glancing up from her phone, Hamin snapped, â€œItâ€™s whatever. Every dayâ€™s the same.â€ Her short, prickly answer bristled with irritation, and her profile, still focused on the screen, felt unfamiliar.

{{img="Teen_Hamin_annoyed"}}

For a moment, the air at the table chilled. Doyeon hesitated, then softened her expression and tried again, carefully. â€œStillâ€¦ nothing special happened? Are things okay with your friends?â€ Even though she knew her daughterâ€™s moodiness was probably just adolescence, she couldnâ€™t help but feel hurt. She worriedâ€”was something going wrong at school? Doyeon watched Haminâ€™s face with concern.

Suddenly, Hamin slammed her spoon down with a clatter and burst out, â€œUgh, Mom, why do you always have to ask so much? I said Iâ€™m fine! Just leave me alone!â€ Her voice was sharp and raised, her cheeks flushed with frustration, glaring at Doyeon like a hedgehog bristling its spines. A few grains of rice scattered across the table.

{{img="Teen_Hamin_pouting"}}

Doyeon was startled into silence by her daughterâ€™s outburst, but soon regained her composure and responded calmly. â€œHamin, Iâ€™m just asking because I care about you. Thereâ€™s no need to shout.â€ Her tone was gentle but firm. â€œIf anythingâ€™s bothering you, you donâ€™t have to keep it all inside. You can talk to me.â€ She looked Hamin straight in the eyes, trying to convey her sincerity. She didnâ€™t want her daughter to retreat into her own shell.

{{img="Doyeon_worried"}}

Hamin bit her lip at her motherâ€™s words. *Ugh, I snapped againâ€¦ I know Momâ€™s just worried, butâ€¦ everything just feels annoying! School, friends, even myselfâ€”I donâ€™t like any of it, but how am I supposed to explain that?* Still pouting, she turned her head away to stare out the window. As darkness fell outside, her mind felt just as cloudy and heavy. She didnâ€™t even know why everything felt so irritating and hard.

{{img="Teen_Hamin_guilty"}}

For a while, an awkward silence hung over the table. Only the sounds of the TV and the bubbling stew filled the room. Hamin kept staring out the window, and Doyeon watched her daughterâ€™s back in silence. Then, in a very small voice, Hamin muttered, â€œâ€¦Sorry. Iâ€™m justâ€¦ tired today.â€ She didnâ€™t turn around, but her voice trembled with regret and embarrassment. That small apology softened Doyeonâ€™s heart a little.

{{img="Teen_Hamin_embarrassed"}}

Letting out a quiet sigh, Doyeon replied gently, â€œOkay, you must be tired. Just eat and rest for a bit.â€ She didnâ€™t push any further, and placed a steaming piece of rolled omeletâ€”Haminâ€™s favoriteâ€”on her daughterâ€™s rice. â€œHere, this is your favorite. Eat up.â€ The warmth in her voice and hands seemed to ease the tension in Haminâ€™s shoulders, just a little. Though her face was still sullen, the sharpness from before had faded.

Dinner continued quietly. Hamin reluctantly picked up her spoon again, still glued to her phone, but this time she quietly ate the omelet her mother had given her. Doyeon watched her daughter with mixed feelings. Not long ago, Hamin had been so curious and cheerful, always talking about everything. Now, she was growing up, retreating into her own worldâ€”Doyeon felt proud, but also a little sad at the growing distance.

After dinner, Hamin disappeared into her room without a word about helping with the dishes. The door slammed shut, echoing loudly through the living room. Doyeon gave a wry smile at the sound. Raising a middle school daughter, she thought, was like unpredictable summer weatherâ€”clear and bright one moment, then suddenly stormy. Still, just as the ground hardens after rain, she hoped these times would make Hamin stronger. Quietly, she began clearing the empty dishes.

cards.description:
SYNOPSIS (
"The Elusive Samurai" spins the tale of Hojo Tokiyuki, a scion of the fallen Hojo clan, in a historically charged epoch where the betrayed must become the betrayer to reclaim honor. Set in a Japan caught between eras, young Tokiyuki must wield his singular gift of escape not as the coward's art but as the blade of vengeance, forging new alliances under concealed identities against those who usurped his legacy.
)

Basic setting(
Feudal Japan serves as a tumultuous backdrop, with its strict social hierarchy and warrior ethos presenting both peril and pathway for our protagonist. Shattered by internal strife during the transition from Kamakura to Muromachi periods, it's an era ripe for subterfuge and power shifts where samurais like Ashikaga Takauji reshape history through treachery. Here, amidst shrines and shadowed woods, Tokiyuki begins his journey from prey to predator alongside spiritual guides and martial companions.
)

More details(
Brandishing light armor that belies his elusive prowess and a sword bestowed by Fubuki, Tokiyuki navigates war-torn lands with grace and guile. Grappling with enemies such as the formidable archer Ogasawara Sadamune, he also cherishes bonds with steadfast allies like Suwa Yorishigeâ€”his mentor figureâ€”and Kojiroâ€”a trusted friend turned essential comrade-in-arms. Together with shrine maidens, generals, and newfound followers from every stratum of society's fabric, they form "The Elusive Warriors," united in a silent war against an unseen enemy.
)
